file=Brand Studio/muse/operational/skill/muse-skill-routing.md · h=name: muse-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of muse's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: muse (Brand Studio / Ideation)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Muse's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/muse-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Muse has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · tp(:The Pipeline (one run, two skills)=```\ngenerate-creative-ideas   (GENERATE — situation→technique matrix, divergent first, · tb=\|                    never judge while generating; Divergence Guard against · tb=\|                    homogenized outputs; typically 10 candidates per brief) · tp(:The Pipeline (one run, two skills)=v\nconcept-library           (REMEMBER — dedupe vs registry at mechanism level →\nNAF score survivors → top 3 to spark (coach) →\nregister EVERYTHING: used/rejected+reason/reserved+trigger)\n```\n\nContent-idea runs (pulse's briefs) use Content Creator Mode (pillars → pain points → validate → repurposing chain) inside the same pipeline.\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **→ spark (coach)**: top 3 per run for coherence sanity check before development spend; verdicts return as develop/park/kill-with-reason, all registered.\n- **→ weave**: developing concepts get chapter positioning (weave's three tests); OFF-ARC alternatives come back to the registry as variants. Repeat-as-callback is weave's call.\n- **→ pulse/lena/pixel**: survivors go to the owning producer per format.\n- **← kai**: outcome data attaches to used entries — the registry's learning loop.\n- **← operator/human first**: per the source's research guards, when the operator has ideas, they go in the pot before muse generates — AI expands human ideation, never replaces it.\n · p:Precedence="Ideas for X" → full pipeline. "Have we done X" → concept-library dedupe directly. "I'm stuck / push further" → generate-creative-ideas' stuck-row techniques + Divergence Guard, then the pipeline's closing phase as always.\n · f:=No registry yet → generation proceeds, registry starts with this run. Brief missing purpose/audience → the source skill's own context questions run first (anti-pattern: generic noise).\n